<DOC><DOCNO> AP880216-0071 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-16-88 1223EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Greece-Refugees     02-16 0158</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Greece-Refugees,0163</SECOND><HEAD>Ship With Romanians, Bulgarian Stowaways Sails to Malta</HEAD><DATELINE>PIRAEUS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A ship carrying 17 stowaways from Romaniaand Bulgaria steamed out of port Tuesday for Malta, although thegroup had requested political asylum in Greece, a port authorityspokesman said.   The Maltese-flagged cargo ship Captain Yiannis set sail sevenhours after docking in Piraeus harbor, said the spokesman, whorequested anonymity.   ``The stowaways asked for asylum as soon as the ship docked andwe started the paperwork but the ship had to leave and they wentwith it,'' the spokesman said.   He said the stowaways, identified only as 16 Romanians and oneBulgarian, had boarded the vessel in Istanbul, Turkey.   It was the third ship carrying refugees to dock in Piraeus inthe past four days.   On Thursday, six Romanians stowaways on two cargo ships fromIstanbul asked for asylum. They were allowed to remain in Greecewhile their requests were being processed.</TEXT></DOC>